description: Numbers that are the sum of 6 positive cubes in exactly 1 way.
comments: It appears that this sequence has 841 terms, the last of which is 19417. This means that all numbers greater than 19417 can be written as the sum of six positive cubes in at least two ways. - T. D. Noe, Dec 13 2006
